---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Wei-Han (Daniel) Chen" description="About Wei-Han (Daniel) Chen: robotics & ML engineer.">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--color-ink)]">About</h1>

    <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-8">
      <img
        src="/images/me/lab-arms.jpg"
        alt="Wei-Han Chen with a dual-arm robot setup"
        class="w-full sm:w-64 h-64 object-cover rounded-lg border border-[var(--color-border)] flex-shrink-0"
      />
      <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-ink-muted)] leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          I'm Wei-Han Chen — I go by Daniel — a robotics and machine learning engineer, and a
          PhD student at Purdue researching multi-robot planning and perception, including
          published work on language-guided active sensing and low-cost collaborative
          planning for multi-arm robot table tennis at Purdue's SCALE Robotics Lab.
        </p>
        <p>
          Alongside my PhD, I'm building <span class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">Vibe</span>, a
          startup developing humanoid robots for the home — I built a humanoid that walks
          reliably for under $300, and a VR teleoperation system for controlling mobile
          robots remotely.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside of research and the startup, I like building things that are a little
          more fun with the same tools — robots that play Connect 4, VR badminton, and
          real-time audio ML for karaoke.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12">
      <h2 class="font-mono text-sm text-[var(--color-ink-muted)] mb-4">// looking for</h2>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-ink)]">
        Internship opportunities in robotics, machine learning, and controls. Reach out at
        <a href="mailto:daniel.weihan.chen@gmail.com" class="text-accent-500 hover:underline">daniel.weihan.chen@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
